giving one line after every test case

Not required as by default the DHCP on eth1 is considered as True in the scenario of
eth0 in static and eth1 in DHCP.
You can call these two TC in one TC by creating template
Yes but this is DHCP related so I don't want to put the system down.

yes, but you are not disturbing eth0 right? you are performing this operation only on eth1....so I think using template will not cause problem to system.It's just my suggestion to reduce lines of codes.
Yes but there will be more test cases coming up, so still prefer not to put as a template.
I believe you always expect the patch to be successful.
Can you please rename the variable
I am asking about ${ethernet_interface}. Where is this defined?
End all statements with a period.
You are just setting the value to True or False in the body. Use it directly instead of using suite variables. Pass '${dhcp_enabled}' to it.
This should not be part of this keyword or you would need to rename the keyword.
Just for pinging the host Redfish Login is not required.
You are doing a patch later in the suite so login is required.
Making sure that the BMC pings, should be part of this test.
Added it in the Suite setup Execution.
As said above this should be part of the test. So add it there and remove it from here.

This keyword is used for enabling/disabling the keyword.
Changing the documentation to make more sense.

Keyword name is in wrong format. Read https://github.com/openbmc/openbmc-test-automation/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md

Separate words with single spaces.
Capitalize the first character of each word.
Capitalize all characters in any word that is an acronym (e.g. JSON, BMC, etc).
Test cases to enable and disable DHCP for eth1

Align to left. 
Add the test case tags in changes
Changing back to data as it needs to take DHCP_ENABLED or DHCP_DISABLED
